GOOGLE SIGN UP / LOGIN FLOW (LARAVEL)

1. USER ACTION

* User opens website
* User clicks "Login with Google" button

2. REDIRECT TO GOOGLE

* Laravel redirects user to Google OAuth page using Socialite

3. USER AUTHENTICATION (GOOGLE SIDE)

* User selects Google account
* User grants permission (email, profile)

4. GOOGLE CALLBACK

* Google redirects back to:
  /auth/google/callback

5. BACKEND PROCESS (LARAVEL)

* Laravel receives user data from Google:

  * name
  * email
  * google_id (id from Google)

6. CHECK USER IN DATABASE

* Query:
  User::where('email', google_email)->first()

7. IF USER DOES NOT EXIST

* Create new user:
  User::create([
  'name' => google_name,
  'email' => google_email,
  'google_id' => google_id,
  'password' => NULL
  ])

8. IF USER EXISTS

* Update google_id if not set (optional)

9. LOGIN USER

* Use Laravel Auth:
  Auth::login($user)

10. REDIRECT

* Redirect to dashboard or homepage

11. OPTIONAL: SEND EMAIL

* Send welcome email ONLY when new user is created

12. ERROR HANDLING

* If login fails → redirect back to login page
* Show error message

13. LOGOUT

* Auth::logout()
* Redirect to login page

---

INSTALLATION STEPS

1. INSTALL SOCIALITE

* Run:
  composer require laravel/socialite

2. ADD CONFIG (config/services.php)

'google' => [
'client_id' => env('GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID'),
'client_secret' => env('GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET'),
'redirect' => env('GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI'),
],

3. ADD ENV VARIABLES (.env)

GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8000/auth/google/callback

---

ROUTES (web.php)

Route::get('/auth/google', [AuthController::class, 'redirectToGoogle']);
Route::get('/auth/google/callback', [AuthController::class, 'handleGoogleCallback']);

---

CONTROLLER (AuthController.php)

use Laravel\Socialite\Facades\Socialite;
use App\Models\User;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Auth;

FUNCTION: redirectToGoogle()

* return Socialite::driver('google')->redirect();

FUNCTION: handleGoogleCallback()

* $googleUser = Socialite::driver('google')->stateless()->user();

* $user = User::where('email', $googleUser->getEmail())->first();

* IF NOT FOUND:
  $user = User::create([
  'name' => $googleUser->getName(),
  'email' => $googleUser->getEmail(),
  'google_id' => $googleUser->getId(),
  'password' => NULL,
  ]);

* Auth::login($user);

* return redirect('/dashboard');

---

DATABASE (USERS TABLE)

Add column:

$table->string('google_id')->nullable();

---

BUTTON (BLADE)

<a href="/auth/google">
  Login with Google
</a>

---

NOTES

* Use stateless() if using API or JWT
* Always keep email UNIQUE
* Google login users don’t need password
* Use HTTPS in production
* Can combine with normal login system

END OF FLOW
